title: How nerve fibers enter spinal cord during early development

title_detail.value: How nerve fibers enter spinal cord during early development

summary: New research could lead to regenerative therapies for people with injuries to their brachial plexus, a group of nerves that starts at the spinal cord and goes into the arm.
